# Workflow Protocol

## Session start
1. Read `docs/superpowers/handoffs/cursor-development-log.md` for last session state.
2. If the task touches business logic or prior decisions, check `docs/decisions/`.
3. If requirements are unclear, invoke `grill-me` before proposing anything.

## Vertical slices
Work in minimal end-to-end slices (DB + backend + UI). Verify each slice before starting the next.

## Skills

| Trigger | Skill file |
|---|---|
| Requirement unclear or scope undefined | `.cursor/skills/grill-me/SKILL.md` |
| Multiple interdependent parts | `.cursor/skills/slice/SKILL.md` |
| New query, server action, or DB type | `.cursor/skills/backend/SKILL.md` |
| UI component, screen, or navigation design | `.cursor/skills/ui-design/SKILL.md` |
| Critical business logic or bugfix with domain impact | `.cursor/skills/testing-quality-gates/SKILL.md` |
| Before declaring any slice done | `.cursor/skills/done/SKILL.md` |

## How to invoke a skill
Reference the file directly in the chat:
> "Seguí el skill: @.cursor/skills/grill-me/SKILL.md"
